Sentencas: Samarium substituted ceria has been studied as a potential electrolyte material for intermediate temperature range solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Comprehensive Analysis of Ce1-xSmxO2-δ Solid Electrolytes: Structural, Microstructural, and Electrochemical Characterization for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The structural, microstructural, morphological and electrochemical properties of the Ce1-xSmxO2-delta solid electrolytes were analyzed, with different substitutions from 0.05 to 0.50.
Titulo: Comprehensive Analysis of Ce1-xSmxO2-δ Solid Electrolytes: Structural, Microstructural, and Electrochemical Characterization for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The difference in the ionic radii of Sm3+ and Ce4+ resulted in lattice strain and expansion, which was found to decrease the average size of crystallites.
Titulo: Comprehensive Analysis of Ce1-xSmxO2-δ Solid Electrolytes: Structural, Microstructural, and Electrochemical Characterization for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The ionic conductivity of ceria increases as Sm3+ concentration is increased upto a limit of 20%.
Titulo: Comprehensive Analysis of Ce1-xSmxO2-δ Solid Electrolytes: Structural, Microstructural, and Electrochemical Characterization for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: This is due to the combination of vacancy-vacancy repulsion and vacancy trapping by the substitution at a higher level.
Titulo: Comprehensive Analysis of Ce1-xSmxO2-δ Solid Electrolytes: Structural, Microstructural, and Electrochemical Characterization for Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The grain activation energy and grain boundary activation energy were also found to be similar to 0.87 eV and similar to 0.74 eV respectively.
